n": false}], "milestone": null, "comments": 4, "created_at": "2021-07-17T18:03:39Z", "updated_at": "2021-10-26T15:15:24Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Currently v0 mangled names don't change when the function abi changes unlike legacy symbol names. This makes it easy to use a rust dynamic library with an incompatible abi at runtime when trying to update rust dynamic libraries the same way as C dynamic libraries for example by a distro either by using an incompatible source or an incompatible rustc version. This may work out fine, but it may also cause crashes or exploitable bugs. There is a test for this, but for some reason it is forced to the legacy symbol mangling scheme only and marked as possibly removable once the legacy scheme gets removed.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c78ebb7bdcfc924a20fd069891ffe1364d6814e7/src/test/run-make-fulldeps/a-b-a-linker-guard/Makefile#L7-L8\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/rust-lang/rust/blob/c78ebb7bdcfc924a20fd069891ffe1364d6814e7/compiler/rustc_symbol_mangling/src/legacy.rs#L118-L123\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_START -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_START$${\"user\":\"pierwill\"}$$TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_DATA_END -->\n\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_ASSIGN_END -->\n<!-- TRIAGEBOT_END -->", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/87223/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/87223/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}